This is not an OSI-approved open source license. It is a purpose-limited, attribution-required,
non-profit-oriented license created for the Digitale Nuts project in the VLAIO City of Things 2025
context.

1. Definitions

"Software" means the code, documentation, and repository materials made available under this license,
excluding third-party components that carry their own license terms.

"Permitted Purpose" means use that materially contributes to one or more of the following public-interest
goals of Digitale Nuts:

- reducing nuisance caused by utility works in the public space;
- improving the quality, speed, traceability, and consistency of follow-up and restoration of utility works;
- supporting a shared data chain between local authorities, utility actors, contractors, GIPOD, and related
  public-interest stakeholders;
- supporting inspection, reporting, communication, KPI monitoring, standardization, training, pilots, or
  operational roll-out in line with the Digitale Nuts City of Things 2025 application context;
- enabling transfer, reuse, or scaling of the above goals for Flemish local authorities or comparable
  public-interest collaborations.

"Derivative Work" means any modified version, extension, adaptation, integration, or redistributed copy of
the Software.

"Cost Recovery" means charging only documented and reasonable amounts needed to cover implementation,
configuration, integration, migration, hosting, infrastructure, maintenance, training, support, compliance,
or public procurement execution costs related to the Permitted Purpose.

2. Grant of Rights

Subject to this license, you may use, copy, study, modify, and share the Software, and create Derivative
Works, only for the Permitted Purpose.

3. Mandatory Conditions

You may exercise the rights above only if all of the following remain true:

- you preserve this license and all existing copyright, attribution, and notice files;
- you clearly mark material changes in redistributed Derivative Works;
- you include the attribution notice from the repository NOTICE file, or an equivalent notice with the same
  substance, in source distributions and in a user-visible location where reasonably possible;
- you do not suggest that Stad Antwerpen, Publieke Ruimte, Nuts, VLAIO, or City of Things endorses your
  version unless you have separate written permission;
- if you distribute a Derivative Work, you must do so under this license or under terms that are not less
  restrictive regarding Permitted Purpose, attribution, non-profit orientation, and downstream obligations.

4. Commercial Restriction

You may not use the Software or any Derivative Work primarily for commercial advantage, profit-seeking
software exploitation, or sale as a proprietary product or service.

The following remains allowed:

- Cost Recovery for work that serves the Permitted Purpose;
- internal or contracted implementation work for local authorities, public-interest partnerships, utilities,
  or comparable actors, provided that the main objective is the Permitted Purpose and not profit extraction
  from the Software itself.

The following is not allowed without separate written permission from the copyright holder:

- selling software licenses based on the Software;
- offering the Software as a standalone commercial SaaS product for profit;
- relicensing the Software or a Derivative Work under a permissive or proprietary commercial license;
- using the Software mainly as a vehicle for private monetization unrelated to the City of Things-style
  public-interest goals described above.

5. Attribution

Every redistributed copy or material Derivative Work must retain the following attribution, or a faithful
equivalent:

"Based on Digitale Nuts Dispatch. Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Stad Antwerpen / Publieke Ruimte / Nuts.
Developed as a starting point for the Digitale Nuts project within the VLAIO City of Things 2025 subsidy
context."

Where practical, the attribution must also mention that reuse must remain aligned with the public-interest
goals of Digitale Nuts.

